    <div class="container">
        <section class="section" id="introduction">
            <h2><i class="fas fa-info-circle icon"></i> Introduction & Overview</h2>
            <div class="card">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <p>Hi Choyon,</p>
                    <p>I'm Helton from <a href="https://brm-extremities.com/" target="_blank">BRM Extremities</a>, an Italian manufacturer specializing in orthopedic medical devices like joint spacers and implants (Class IIa/IIb/III under EU MDR). We're expanding globally, but regulatory compliance is a bottleneck. Distributors in places like Ukraine over-request documents, raising suspicions, while novices in the US (e.g., Texas) need guidance on import processes.</p>
                    <p>This tool adapts the <a href="https://github.com/harindermashiana/sec-10q-rag" target="_blank">sec-10q-rag</a> repo's RAG architecture (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) from SEC financial filings to medical device regulations. It will ingest official docs, enable semantic searches, and generate comparisons/checklists via LLM.</p>
                    <p><strong>Why you?</strong> Your 5.0 rating (823 reviews) and expertise in Python automation, web scraping, Selenium, APIs (Flask/Django), data processing, and bots make you ideal. We'll solve real problems while building something scalable.</p>
                    <p><strong>High-Level Benefits:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Save hours on manual research.</li>
                        <li>Flag fraudulent over-requests (e.g., Ukraine).</li>
                        <li>Generate ready-to-share guides (e.g., US imports).</li>
                        <li>Scale to new markets with minimal updates.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>Let's make this perfect – detailed, actionable, and user-friendly!</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="section" id="problems">
            <h2><i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle icon"></i> Core Problems to Solve</h2>
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-6">
                    <div class="card">
                        <div class="card-body">
                            <h3>Scenario 1: Ukraine Distributor Suspicion</h3>
                            <p>A distributor requests excessive docs for product registration. We suspect extras (e.g., unrelated financials). Tool must:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Ingest MoH/SEC docs (Resolutions 753-755, HTA Order 1771 – new as of Nov 2025 for high-risk devices).</li>
                                <li>Allow upload of requested list (text/CSV).</li>
                                <li>Compare semantically: Flag extras/mismatches with explanations (e.g., "Financial audit not required per Res. 753").</li>
                                <li>Query examples: "Is a bank statement mandatory for Class IIb implants?" or "Full list for orthopedic registration."</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p><strong>In-Depth Rationale:</strong> Ukraine aligns with EU but has local twists (e.g., AR mandatory, Ukrainian translations). 2026 updates include stricter HTA for implants – tool auto-detects changes.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-6">
                    <div class="card">
                        <div class="card-body">
                            <h3>Scenario 2: US (Texas) Novice Importer Guidance</h3>
                            <p>New distributor lacks import experience. We have FDA 510(k), but need to split guidance: Their docs vs. ours per shipment. Tool must:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Ingest FDA guides (21 CFR 801-820, QMSR effective Feb 2026 – ISO 13485 alignment).</li>
                                <li>Generate role-based checklists (Importer: FEI reg, affirmations; Exporter: CFG cert, invoices).</li>
                                <li>Customize: "For first-time import of Italian orthopedic devices."</li>
                                <li>Export to PDF for sharing.</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p><strong>In-Depth Rationale:</strong> No Texas-specific rules (federal only), but CBP/FDA entry can delay shipments. QMSR 2026 mandates quality system audits – include notes on compliance evidence.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="section" id="mvp">
            <h2><i class="fas fa-rocket icon"></i> MVP Goals & Features</h2>
            <div class="card">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <p><strong>Scope:</strong> 15 priority countries (expandable). Focus on orthopedic/Class IIa+ devices. User queries in English/Portuguese.</p>
                    <h3>Key Features (In-Depth)</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Natural Language Queries:</strong> Semantic search e.g., "Docs for Class IIb registration in China?" Outputs structured tables with sources.</li>
                        <li><strong>Comparison Mode:</strong> Upload distributor list; LLM analyzes diffs (use cosine similarity on embeddings for accuracy). Flag levels: Required/Missing/Extra/Optional.</li>
                        <li><strong>Checklist Generator:</strong> Role-split (Importer/Exporter/Manufacturer), customizable by device class/country. Include timelines/costs where available.</li>
                        <li><strong>Translation & Updates:</strong> Auto-translate (googletrans/DeepL); monthly cron scrape for changes (diff old/new versions, notify via email).</li>
                        <li><strong>Disclaimers & Logging:</strong> Every output: "Not legal advice." Log queries for auditing.</li>
                        <li><strong>Extensibility:</strong> Admin dashboard to upload new docs/countries; modular config (YAML for sources).</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p><strong>Example User Flow:</strong> Login → Select country → Query or upload list → View table/checklist → Export PDF.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

