        <section class="section" id="tech">
            <h2><i class="fas fa-code icon"></i> Tech Stack & Architecture</h2>
            <div class="card">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <p><strong>Base:</strong> Fork <a href="https://github.com/harindermashiana/sec-10q-rag" target="_blank">sec-10q-rag</a> – modular Python package with ingestion, embedding, and querying.</p>
                    <h3>Components (In-Depth)</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Language:</strong> Python 3.9+ (use venv for isolation).</li>
                        <li><strong>Ingestion:</strong> Requests/BeautifulSoup/Selenium for scraping (handle anti-bot with headers/rotating proxies). PyMuPDF/langchain for PDF/HTML parsing (extract sections via regex/heuristics, e.g., "Article X: Requirements").</li>
                        <li><strong>Processing:</strong> Chunk to 500-1000 tokens; translate non-English (googletrans free; fallback DeepL if API key provided). Clean noise (headers/footers).</li>
                        <li><strong>Embeddings/Search:</strong> SentenceTransformers (all-MiniLM-L6-v2 for multilingual); FAISS index (hybrid dense/sparse for precision). Tag by country/section/device class.</li>
                        <li><strong>LLM:</strong> OpenAI GPT-4o-mini (provide key securely); custom prompts for comparisons (e.g., "Analyze [context] vs [user_list]: Output JSON {required: [], extras: []}"). Fallback local (HuggingFace Llama-3 via transformers).</li>
                        <li><strong>Storage:</strong> SQLite (metadata: doc URLs, versions, tags); local JSON/FAISS for embeddings (persistent across runs).</li>
                        <li><strong>Interface:</strong> Flask web app (Bootstrap for UI); routes: /query, /compare, /checklist. File upload (Werkzeug); PDF export (ReportLab or WeasyPrint).</li>
                        <li><strong>Other:</strong> Logging (logging lib); error handling (e.g., retry failed scrapes); security (sanitize inputs, API key env vars).</li>
                    </ul>
                    <h3>Sample Code Snippet: Basic Query Prompt</h3>
                    <pre class="code-snippet">
prompt = f"""
Based on the following regulatory context for {country}:
{context_chunks}
Answer the query: {user_query}
Output in markdown table format with columns: Document, Requirement, Details, Source.
Include disclaimer.
"""
response = openai.ChatCompletion.create(model="gpt-4o-mini", messages=[{"role": "user", "content": prompt}])
                    </pre>
                    <h3>Architecture Diagram (Text-Based)</h3>
                    <pre class="code-snippet">
User Query/UI → Query Engine (Filter by Country) → FAISS Retrieval (Top-K Chunks) → LLM Prompt Builder → OpenAI Response → Output Formatter (Table/PDF)
Parallel: Scraper Cron → Parser → Embedder → Update Index
                    </pre>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="section" id="theming">
            <h2><i class="fas fa-palette icon"></i> Theming Instructions for UI/UX</h2>
            <div class="card">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <p>To ensure the tool aligns with BRM Extremities' branding, theme the entire UI/UX to match our corporate identity. This creates a seamless, professional experience that reflects our focus on innovation in orthopedic medical devices.</p>
                    <h3>Key Branding Elements</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Color Scheme:</strong> Primary: #007bff (vibrant blue for trust and health); Secondary: #004085 (deep navy for depth); Accents: #ffffff (white for cleanliness), #e6f0ff (light blue for backgrounds); Gradients: Use linear-gradient(135deg, #007bff, #004085) for headers/buttons.</li>
                        <li><strong>Fonts:</strong> Main: 'Montserrat' (sans-serif, weights 400/600/800 for modern, readable look); Code/Technical: 'Courier New' or monospace. Import via Google Fonts.</li>
                        <li><strong>Logo Integration:</strong> Include our logo (URL: <a href="https://brm-extremities.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Logo-BRM-Extremities.png" target="_blank">Logo</a>) in the header/navigation. Make it clickable to our site. Use drop-shadow for elevation.</li>
                        <li><strong>Layout & Style:</strong> Clean, minimalistic medical theme – white/light blue backgrounds, rounded corners (15-20px radius), subtle shadows (e.g., box-shadow: 0 10px 20px rgba(0, 64, 133, 0.15)). Buttons: Gradient blue, rounded (50px), hover effects (scale 1.08, shadow). Tables: Blue headers, light borders (#b3d1ff).</li>
                        <li><strong>Icons & Animations:</strong> Use Font Awesome icons in blue (#007bff). Subtle animations: Shine effect on header, hover translates/lifts on cards/links.</li>
                        <li><strong>Responsive Design:</strong> Mobile-first with Bootstrap; ensure clean stacking on small screens.</li>
                        <li><strong>Additional Notes:</strong> Match our website's style (<a href="https://brm-extremities.com/" target="_blank">brm-extremities.com</a>) – professional, trustworthy, with blue accents for Italian excellence in medtech. Add footer with copyright and link to our site.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p><strong>Implementation:</strong> Use Bootstrap 5+ for base, override with custom CSS. Test on desktop/mobile. This spec page itself is themed as an example – replicate similar styles in the tool's Flask app.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="section" id="plan">
            <h2><i class="fas fa-calendar-check icon"></i> Development Plan & Milestones</h2>
            <div class="card">
